comments.text: T97A is a polymorphic accessory mutation that, depending on subtype, occurs in 1% to 5% of viruses from untreated persons. It is selected by RAL and EVG. Alone, it has minimal effects on INSTI susceptibility but in combination with other major resistance mutations, particularly Y143C/R, it synergistically reduces susceptibility to EVG and RAL.
